data.enText: a part of an area of activity, especially of a country's economy
service-sector jobs (= in hotels, restaurants, etc.)
a part of a particular area, especially an area under military control
each sector of the war zone

simple_means.memory_skill: sect 切，割 + or 表名词 → 部分；部门

tr: measuring instrument consisting of two graduated arms hinged at one end
a particular aspect of life or activity
example: he was helpless in an important sector of his life

tr: a social group that forms part of the society or the economy
a portion of a military position
the minimum track length that can be assigned to store information
unless otherwise specified a sector of data consists of 512 bytes
a plane figure bounded by two radii and the included arc of a circle

value.def: A particular sector of a country's economy is the part connected with that specified type of industry.

example.ex: ...the service sector of the Hong Kong economy.
example.tran: 香港经济中的服务行业

value.def: A sector of a large group is a smaller group which is part of it.

example.ex: Workers who went to the Gulf came from the poorest sectors of Pakistani society.
example.tran: 前往海湾的工人来自巴基斯坦最贫穷的社会阶层。

value.def: A sector is an area of a city or country which is controlled by a military force.

example.ex: Officers were going to retake sectors of the city.
example.tran: 军官们打算重新夺回该市的防御区。

value.tran: 军事管制区;军事防御区

value.def: A sector is a part of a circle which is formed when you draw two straight lines from the centre of the circle to the edge.

partsOfSpeech.dec: bi 二 + sect 切，割 → 二等分
dis 加强 + sect 切，割 → 切分 → 解剖
dissect 解剖 + ion 表名词 → 解剖
inter 在…之间 + sect 切，割 → 从中间切开 → 横切
intersect 横切；交叉 + ion 表名词 → 横切；交叉
sect 切，割 + ion 表名词 → 切开；部门
section 切开；部门 + al …的 → 可组合的；部门的
sect 切，割 + or 表名词 → 部分；部门
seg 切，割 + ment 具体物 → 切开后的东西 → 切片
segment 部分；切片 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 割成几部分 → 分裂
tran〔= trans 横〕+ sect 切，割 → 横着切 → 横断
vivi 活 + sect 切，割 → 活着切开 → 活体解剖
